<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 05 at 7:15PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Macon,
northeastern Marion, Schley and southern Taylor Counties through 745
PM EDT...
At 715 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Rupert, or 10 miles
south of Butler, moving south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ellaville, Oglethorpe, Montezuma, Ideal, Murrays Crossroads,
Whitewater State Park, Fountainville, Rupert, Charing, Garden Valley,
Hicks, Potterville, Mauk, Clearview, Bartlett and Walls Crossing.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
